Senior high school students are set to return to campus on 27 April, and senior students at middle schools will return to campus on 11 May. SHANGHAI/BEIJING - Beijing schools closed by the coronavirus outbreak will reopen to senior high school students and senior middle school students, state broadcaster CCTV reported on Sunday, citing a spokesman for the Beijing Municipal Education Commission. Senior high school students are set to return to campus on 27 April, and senior students at middle schools will return to campus on 11 May, said spokesman Li Yi at a press conference, according to the CCTV report.